*How can you tell whether you need `pivot_longer` or `pivot_wider`?*

* I can tell when I need pivot_longer vs pivot_wider based on how I want my data to look. If I want the data to look like fewer columns and more rows, I'd use pivot_longer. On the flip side, if I wanted my data to show a lot of columns and only the few rows, I'd use pivot_wider. It seems that at least with one-sided tables, pivot longer puts variables across the top and pivot_wider puts the variables down the side.



